{{nihongo|'''Chōfu Aerospace Center'''|調布航空宇宙センター|Chōfu Kōkū-uchū senta}} is the headquarters and main development facility for the [[Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency]] (JAXA).
The Chōfu Aerospace Center concentrates on [[aerospace engineering]] research and development, and is equipped with test facilities including several [[wind tunnel]]s, materials test facilities, [[flight simulator]]s, engine test stands and a [[supercomputer]].
